      "writtenOn": "2020-09-14T15:38:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general this looks fine. Can you remind me what exactly a bind group is in Dawn? Like are we creating a different bind group for each uniform buffer or is it the data of the uniforms themselves? Like if I have the same GrDawnProgram but change a uniform value I get a new bindGroup?",
      "revId": "82958e4eff67af00c05a330de5acebaec3f4f98c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ec86a46a_77838d69",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5290
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-14T16:16:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In Vulkan terms, it\u0027s a descriptor set. It can point to uniform buffers, storage buffers, samplers, textures, etc. The Dawn backend uses one BindGroup for UBOs and one for samplers and textures. Right now, we create a new uniform BindGroup each time the the uniform values change. They\u0027re cached internally in Dawn, but still can be a perf bottleneck.",
      "parentUuid": "e364d606_12e43371",
      "revId": "82958e4eff67af00c05a330de5acebaec3f4f98c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
